devdoc.author: Gustavo Valverde
devdoc.custom:concept: Storing encrypted identity attributes (euint8, euint16, ebool)
devdoc.custom:difficulty: intermediate This contract maintains an encrypted identity registry where authorized registrars (typically a backend service) can attest to user identity attributes. All sensitive data remains encrypted on-chain. Key patterns demonstrated: 1. Multiple encrypted types (euint8, euint16, ebool) 2. Role-based access control (registrars) 3. Struct-like data storage with mappings 4. FHE permission management (allowThis, allow)

params.user: Address of the user granting access

params.registrar: Address of the registrar who performed attestation

params.attestationId: Monotonic attestation identifier for the user
params.registrar: Address of the registrar who performed attestation
